17,500 feet above Quantico, Virginia,

00:05:40.948 --> 00:05:43.768
and covers 15 square miles.

00:05:44.238 --> 00:05:47.788
Yiannis Antoniades: This whole image
is at a very, very fine resolution.

00:05:47.788 --> 00:05:52.638
So if we wanted to know what's going on
in any spot along this image,

00:05:52.638 --> 00:05:55.308
let's say near this building
at this intersection,

00:05:55.308 --> 00:05:59.938
everything that is a moving object
is being automatically tracked.

00:05:59.938 --> 00:06:01.713
The color boxes represent

00:06:01.720 --> 00:06:04.788
that the computer has recognized
the moving objects.

00:06:05.028 --> 00:06:07.538
You can see individuals
crossing the street.

00:06:07.608 --> 00:06:10.388
You can see individuals
walking in parking lots.

00:06:10.718 --> 00:06:12.777
There's actually enough resolution

00:06:12.777 --> 00:06:15.907
to be able to see the people
waving their arms

00:06:15.907 --> 00:06:18.527
or walking around
and what kind of clothes they wear.

00:06:19.649 --> 00:06:23.389
Narrator: Unlike the predator camera
that limits field of view,

00:06:23.389 --> 00:06:27.843
ARGUS-IS melts together videos
from each of its 368 chips

00:06:27.843 --> 00:06:32.073
to create a 1.8 billion
pixel video stream.

00:06:32.943 --> 00:06:38.177
This makes it possible to zoom in
and still see tremendous detail.

00:06:38.657 --> 00:06:43.901
Jay Tuck: And it produces
a million terabytes every day.

00:06:43.901 --> 00:06:45.256
That's a lot of data.

00:06:45.256 --> 00:06:46.774
I'm telling you this because -

00:06:46.777 --> 00:06:50.734
not that the sensors are modern
and not that the photography is modern -

00:06:50.734 --> 00:06:55.144
behind that is a brain,
or a cognitive intelligence,

00:06:55.670 --> 00:07:01.350
and that brain is in a position
to analyze everybody down there.

00:07:02.240 --> 00:07:06.210
At the same time, in real time,
they see where everyone is going.

00:07:06.240 --> 00:07:09.052
We can understand that
when we reduce it to a single person,

00:07:09.052 --> 00:07:10.404
but we can't understand it

00:07:10.404 --> 00:07:15.110
when you're talking about
a hundred thousand people in a city,

00:07:15.110 --> 00:07:18.240
plus the vehicles
which are all recognized.

00:07:18.841 --> 00:07:21.754
Due to such systems, they have
also redone facial recognition.

00:07:21.754 --> 00:07:25.500
You probably think facial
recognition is from the front,

00:07:25.500 --> 00:07:27.880
but they've redone it
to do it from the top

00:07:27.880 --> 00:07:29.600
because that's where the drones are.

00:07:29.600 --> 00:07:32.760
They look at your ears,
the way you walk, your head -

00:07:32.760 --> 00:07:35.370
that's modern facial recognition.

00:07:36.201 --> 00:07:41.681
So, that's one idea: as a human being,
we think of one camera and one person.

00:07:43.197 --> 00:07:46.231
This is a little of their things:

00:07:46.231 --> 00:07:50.415
It's taking all the details,
all the musing after, and then record it,

00:07:50.418 --> 00:07:54.175
so they can tell where that person was
two weeks ago, two months ago,

00:07:54.175 --> 00:07:58.015
what stores he visited,
what his whole behavioral patterns are.

00:07:58.015 --> 00:08:01.859
That's all part of the analysis of Argus.

00:08:02.876 --> 00:08:07.916
These are called "tennis balls"
in military and intelligence circles.

00:08:08.268 --> 00:08:11.558
It's a new secretive sensoric thing.

00:08:11.558 --> 00:08:15.128
Cruise missile would fly
into a valley in Afghanistan -

00:08:15.128 --> 00:08:19.868
this is especially important because
the troops have left many of these areas -

00:08:19.868 --> 00:08:24.858
and would drop literally thousands
of these sensor packages or tennis balls -

00:08:24.858 --> 00:08:27.447
they're all packed in foam rubber.

00:08:28.034 --> 00:08:30.084
They record with cameras.

00:08:30.084 --> 00:08:32.034
They record with microphones.

00:08:32.034 --> 00:08:34.520
They record with seismic measurements.

00:08:34.520 --> 00:08:36.493
They record with Geiger counters.

00:08:36.493 --> 00:08:40.801
They record with chemical sensors,
they can look for chemical things.

00:08:40.801 --> 00:08:42.504
That's not the amazing part of it,

00:08:42.504 --> 00:08:45.918
and it's not the amazing part
that their signal goes to a transmitter

00:08:45.918 --> 00:08:47.310
and then up to the satellite:

00:08:47.310 --> 00:08:49.930
old technology, nothing special.

00:08:50.287 --> 00:08:52.277
The special part of it is,

00:08:52.277 --> 00:08:56.857
behind that system,
there's a fusion software

00:08:56.857 --> 00:09:02.027
that can combine the audio and the visual
and the seismic and the chemical,

00:09:02.027 --> 00:09:05.177
all of these signals,
and make sense of them,

00:09:05.177 --> 00:09:09.087
and analyze on the ground
what kind of troop movements there are,

00:09:09.087 --> 00:09:12.097
the kinds of vehicles they're using,
what are they transporting,

00:09:12.097 --> 00:09:13.937
and if there's radioactivity in that.

00:09:13.937 --> 00:09:16.685
It takes all these different
pieces of information

00:09:16.685 --> 00:09:21.155
and turns it through fusion software
into an understandable picture

00:09:21.155 --> 00:09:25.805
which goes way beyond,
way beyond our vision.

00:09:27.160 --> 00:09:32.180
Artificial intelligence only works
if you have huge data masses.

00:09:32.840 --> 00:09:36.970
Artificial intelligence only works
if you have big data,

00:09:36.970 --> 00:09:38.360
but big data only works

00:09:38.360 --> 00:09:40.930
if you have artificial intelligence
to make sense of it

00:09:40.930 --> 00:09:44.850
because human beings can
no longer sort and sift and order

00:09:44.850 --> 00:09:48.150
the huge volumes of data
that we have collected.

00:09:48.635 --> 00:09:50.355
(Music)

00:09:50.941 --> 00:09:53.681
And thus it is not surprising

00:09:53.681 --> 00:09:57.571
that the company that has
the most information in the world -

00:09:57.571 --> 00:10:00.351
it's probably the most powerful
company in the world -

00:10:00.351 --> 00:10:01.891
Google,

00:10:01.891 --> 00:10:04.551
is very interested
in artificial intelligence

00:10:04.551 --> 00:10:07.771
and has been travelling
around the world as a shopping queen,

00:10:07.771 --> 00:10:10.621
buying all the companies
that are dealing with robotics -

00:10:10.621 --> 00:10:13.851
this is one of their robots called Atlas.

00:10:14.251 --> 00:10:16.360
They're buying
our artificial intelligence,

00:10:16.360 --> 00:10:20.340
all the artificial intelligence companies
from around the world.

00:10:20.510 --> 00:10:22.910
Now, if you ask Google,

00:10:24.120 --> 00:10:25.770
it's a peaceful robot, right?

00:10:25.770 --> 00:10:29.163
He doesn't have a gun;
he doesn't throw atomic bombs.

00:10:29.163 --> 00:10:32.663
He just walks around and stands there.

00:10:32.663 --> 00:10:36.213
But you may have seen
the superimposes of DARPA -

00:10:36.213 --> 00:10:39.873
Defense Advanced
Research Projects Agency.

00:10:39.873 --> 00:10:44.123
That is the research arm of the Pentagon.

00:10:44.625 --> 00:10:48.305
Then, you see the video
is made by Lockheed Martin,

00:10:48.305 --> 00:10:51.904
which is one of the most
powerful and influential

00:10:51.904 --> 00:10:56.174
and richest weapons
companies in the world.

00:10:56.334 --> 00:10:58.794
So why is the Pentagon
investing this money?

00:10:58.794 --> 00:11:03.754
Why has Lockheed Martin
taken over large aspects of the company?

00:11:04.391 --> 00:11:06.031
This guy is called "Big Dog."

00:11:06.031 --> 00:11:09.861
He also belongs to Google,
also DARPA financed.

00:11:09.861 --> 00:11:11.711
Peaceful dog, right?

00:11:11.900 --> 00:11:15.520
Unless he gets caught on a maneuver
with the United States Marines,

00:11:15.520 --> 00:11:17.720
as part of a military unit.

00:11:18.443 --> 00:11:21.073
So, these are not flower children.

00:11:21.343 --> 00:11:23.503
These are robots that have a function.

00:11:23.503 --> 00:11:25.953
And robots that have
a function and an intelligence,

00:11:25.953 --> 00:11:30.183
and perhaps an intelligence that goes
beyond us, are dangerous things.

00:11:30.344 --> 00:11:32.194
Now that's a Predator drone;

00:11:32.194 --> 00:11:35.704
this was taken at a secret United States
Air Force base in New Mexico.

00:11:36.445 --> 00:11:40.365
Predator drones, you've seen them, right?
On TV, in the newspapers ...

00:11:40.573 --> 00:11:44.530
They're old!
They're 20-years-old technology.

00:11:44.808 --> 00:11:48.104
It looks very scary
when the Spiegel and the ARD

00:11:48.104 --> 00:11:50.935
write about modern technology
and the guys with a joystick

00:11:50.935 --> 00:11:56.056
that are killing people and Taliban
in Afghanistan far away,

00:11:56.716 --> 00:12:00.196
but that's what a modern drone looks like.

00:12:00.336 --> 00:12:05.386
This is not a Predator; it's a Pegasus,
an X-47B owned by the Navy.

00:12:05.579 --> 00:12:09.164
It's a jet-powered machine
not like a propeller-driven Predator.

00:12:09.164 --> 00:12:12.574
It goes 2,000 miles into enemy territory.

00:12:12.574 --> 00:12:15.885
It carries 2,000 kilos
worth of explosives,

00:12:15.885 --> 00:12:17.854
and it's run by artificial intelligence.

00:12:17.871 --> 00:12:19.581
It starts alone,

00:12:19.581 --> 00:12:21.501
flies its mission alone,

00:12:21.501 --> 00:12:23.271
comes back alone,

00:12:23.271 --> 00:12:27.781
and here's the clue, it lands
all by itself on an aircraft carrier.

00:12:28.407 --> 00:12:30.515
Talk to any pilot you've ever met:

00:12:30.515 --> 00:12:33.555
what's the most difficult landing area
you can possibly imagine?

00:12:33.555 --> 00:12:37.735
They'd say it's an aircraft carrier -
short runway, thing's moving - very hard.

00:12:37.735 --> 00:12:42.915
This thinking drone can do it, 
but here are the two keys to Pegasus.

00:12:44.249 --> 00:12:46.629
Pegasus is invisible.

00:12:47.443 --> 00:12:50.363
I'm not talking about stealth
and being invisible to radar.

00:12:50.363 --> 00:12:53.468
I'm talking about invisible
to the human eye,

00:12:53.473 --> 00:12:56.343
and you won't find this
in any newspaper anywhere.

00:12:56.343 --> 00:13:02.743
It's invisible to the human eye
because the bottom has an LED layer on it,

00:13:02.743 --> 00:13:04.427
and the top has cameras,

00:13:04.434 --> 00:13:07.420
which have been removed
here in the picture,

00:13:07.420 --> 00:13:09.810
which film the sky,
and they project on the bottom

00:13:09.810 --> 00:13:12.550
a live picture of clouds
up above the aircraft,

00:13:12.550 --> 00:13:14.470
and you can hardly see it.

00:13:14.470 --> 00:13:17.770
They're responsible for a lot
of these UFO sightings

00:13:17.770 --> 00:13:19.980
in Nevada, near the testing areas.

00:13:20.220 --> 00:13:25.357
Jet engine propulsion,
a reach of 2,000 miles,

00:13:25.357 --> 00:13:27.648
start and landing all by itself,

00:13:27.648 --> 00:13:31.497
stealth is optical stealth -
you can't see it - and ...

00:13:32.107 --> 00:13:34.411
the kill decision,

00:13:34.411 --> 00:13:38.261
which is required by United States law
to be made by human beings -

00:13:38.261 --> 00:13:42.745
human beings must be in the loop
before someone is killed by a drone -

00:13:42.745 --> 00:13:46.586
is in the machine,
and it doesn't need people.

00:13:46.586 --> 00:13:51.506
It can decide by itself
whether or not it kills somebody.

00:13:52.131 --> 00:13:56.181
The experts say it's going to make
less mistakes and less collateral damage

00:13:56.181 --> 00:13:58.211
than the human decisions.

00:13:59.121 --> 00:14:03.121
The kill decision in robots in the air,
in robots on the ground,

00:14:03.121 --> 00:14:07.931
in robots in the water or underwater,
where there are also drones,

00:14:07.931 --> 00:14:11.441
is made by or can be made by machines.

00:14:11.670 --> 00:14:15.072
In my book, I quote many official
United States government documents

00:14:15.072 --> 00:14:19.612
which say, "Our goal is to have
the kill decision made by them."

00:14:19.612 --> 00:14:23.762
The problem is,
artificial intelligence sometimes ...

00:14:26.118 --> 00:14:27.948
makes mistakes.

00:14:28.214 --> 00:14:30.754
This is Talon, an automatic cannon.

00:14:30.754 --> 00:14:33.764
You can put a lot
of ammunition in that thing,

00:14:33.764 --> 00:14:35.784
and you can also put rockets on it.

00:14:35.784 --> 00:14:38.564
It's in Iraq since 2007.

00:14:38.734 --> 00:14:43.604
At a demonstration
with US generals and experts,

00:14:44.178 --> 00:14:46.588
the damn thing got out of control

00:14:46.588 --> 00:14:50.138
and started pointing at the audience.

00:14:50.638 --> 00:14:53.928
There was a marine there, thank goodness,

00:14:53.928 --> 00:14:56.968
running across the field, 
who tackled it like a football player

00:14:56.968 --> 00:14:58.718
and threw it on its side,

00:14:58.718 --> 00:15:02.568
and probably prevented
a couple hundred people from being killed.

00:15:02.931 --> 00:15:04.326
This was not a reason enough

00:15:04.326 --> 00:15:09.081
to take a lucrative contract
away from the company that built it,

00:15:09.081 --> 00:15:11.581
and it wasn't enough
to take the Talon out of Iraq.

00:15:11.581 --> 00:15:13.651
It's just sort of off-duty for a moment

00:15:13.651 --> 00:15:16.041
because, you know,

00:15:16.041 --> 00:15:20.741
there were some "early stages
of development," that kind of problem.

00:15:21.468 --> 00:15:23.929
But don't underestimate
artificial intelligence,

00:15:23.929 --> 00:15:27.649
because it's getting better every day,

00:15:28.129 --> 00:15:30.459
and it's going to scare us.

00:15:30.830 --> 00:15:33.660
I'm right at the right time,
why is it saying "stop"?

00:15:34.263 --> 00:15:38.895
Because ... This has all been
here-and-now technology,

00:15:38.895 --> 00:15:41.224
let's go to the future, not far,

00:15:41.224 --> 00:15:44.284
just a little bit
to the Internet of things,

00:15:44.284 --> 00:15:49.328
to artificial intelligence
as being spread out.

00:15:49.328 --> 00:15:52.448
It's not a central machine in a box
where you can pull the plug.

00:15:52.448 --> 00:15:55.658
Artificial intelligence is networked,
like the Internet of things,

00:15:55.658 --> 00:16:00.408
and part of it may be in a smart watch
or a refrigerator or in a supercomputer.

00:16:00.579 --> 00:16:05.129
The intelligence exists only
by networking it together.

00:16:05.503 --> 00:16:09.203
If the supercomputer needs
more computer power,

00:16:09.203 --> 00:16:11.523
it goes there and gets it
out of the Internet.

00:16:11.523 --> 00:16:15.933
If the computer needs better programs,
it goes there and gets those programs.

00:16:15.933 --> 00:16:18.273
And if it needs more
information, more data,

00:16:18.273 --> 00:16:20.033
it goes there and gets more data.

00:16:20.033 --> 00:16:23.553
It sets up a spontaneous
network for its needs,

00:16:23.553 --> 00:16:26.855
which collapses
when it no longer needs it.

00:16:28.946 --> 00:16:31.126
It does this without us.

00:16:31.432 --> 00:16:35.522
You have to imagine there are these
intelligence nodes all over the place,

00:16:35.522 --> 00:16:38.692
and they're like drops
of mercury on a glass table.

00:16:38.782 --> 00:16:41.762
They will find their way to each other.

00:16:41.762 --> 00:16:44.452
They will find their way together.

00:16:45.301 --> 00:16:48.681
Now, we have to be very careful

00:16:48.681 --> 00:16:52.921
because survival is an issue
for artificial intelligence.

00:16:53.177 --> 00:16:54.407
It needs to exist

00:16:54.411 --> 00:16:58.187
to be able to do the things
it wants to do according to its program.

00:16:58.187 --> 00:17:01.413
So it lays, like insect eggs,

00:17:01.413 --> 00:17:05.217
backups in computer programs
all over the world,

00:17:05.217 --> 00:17:07.177
thousands and thousands of them,

00:17:07.177 --> 00:17:09.887
so that if we do destroy part of it,

00:17:10.651 --> 00:17:12.471
it's still alive.

00:17:12.888 --> 00:17:15.418
My job to you

00:17:16.445 --> 00:17:20.445
is the wake-up call
to make you aware of the problem.

00:17:20.977 --> 00:17:24.607
Your job is to figure out
how we're going to stop this

00:17:24.811 --> 00:17:26.731
before it kills us.

00:17:26.992 --> 00:17:28.462
Thank you.

00:17:28.462 --> 00:17:30.262
(Applause)

